<p>
A <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Cube.html">cube</a> can be const=
ructed from the dodecahedron's vertices taken eight at a time (above left f=
igure; Steinhaus 1999, pp.&nbsp;198-199; Wells
 1991). Five such cubes can be constructed, forming the <a href=3D"https://=
mathworld.wolfram.com/Cube5-Compound.html">cube
 5-compound</a>. In addition, joining the centers of the faces gives three =
mutually
 <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Perpendicular.html">perpendicular=
</a> <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/GoldenRectangle.html">golden
 rectangles</a> (right figure; Wells 1991).
</p>
<div class=3D"center-image">
